The article announces several nominations and appointments made by President Donald J. Trump. Michele A. Pearce from Virginia has been nominated to be the General Counsel of the Department of the Army. She currently serves as the Principal Deputy General Counsel of the United States Army and has held various senior roles in the Department of Defense and Congress. Ashok Pinto from Illinois has been nominated to be the United States Alternate Executive Director of the International Bank for Reconstruction and Development. He currently serves as Counselor to the Under Secretary for International Affairs at the United States Department of the Treasury and has held senior leadership roles in Congress and the White House. Additionally, President Trump announced his intent to appoint Joseph Douek from New York as a Member of the Commission for the Preservation of America's Heritage Abroad, and Gary B. Heck from California as a Member of the Advisory Committee for Trade Policy and Negotiations.